# The `ilist_node.h` File Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

This file defines the ilist&#95;node class template, which is a convenient base class for creating classes that can be used with ilists. <a href="#details">More...</a>

## Description {#details}

This file defines the ilist&#95;node class template, which is a convenient base class for creating classes that can be used with ilists.

<Link id="l00146" /><CodeLine lineNumber="146"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Check whether this is the sentinel node.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00147" /><CodeLine lineNumber="147"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00148" /><CodeLine lineNumber="148"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// This requires sentinel tracking to be explicitly enabled.  Use the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00149" /><CodeLine lineNumber="149"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// ilist&#95;sentinel&#95;tracking&lt;true&gt; option to get this API.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00150" /><CodeLine lineNumber="150" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/ilist-node-impl/#a0570092282570244c4d7af86003f0aa9"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/ilist-node-impl/#a0570092282570244c4d7af86003f0aa9">isSentinel</a>()</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword"> const </span><span class="doxyHighlight">&#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00156" /><CodeLine lineNumber="156"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00157" /><CodeLine lineNumber="157"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// An intrusive list node.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00158" /><CodeLine lineNumber="158"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00159" /><CodeLine lineNumber="159"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// A base class to enable membership in intrusive lists, including \\a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00160" /><CodeLine lineNumber="160"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// simple&#95;ilist, \\a iplist, and \\a ilist.  The first template parameter is the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00161" /><CodeLine lineNumber="161"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\a value&#95;type for the list.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00162" /><CodeLine lineNumber="162"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00163" /><CodeLine lineNumber="163"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// An ilist node can be configured with compile-time options to change</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00164" /><CodeLine lineNumber="164"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// behaviour and/or add API.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00165" /><CodeLine lineNumber="165"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00166" /><CodeLine lineNumber="166"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// By default, an \\a ilist&#95;node knows whether it is the list sentinel (an</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00167" /><CodeLine lineNumber="167"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// instance of \\a ilist&#95;sentinel) if and only if</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00168" /><CodeLine lineNumber="168"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// LLVM&#95;ENABLE&#95;ABI&#95;BREAKING&#95;CHECKS.  The function \\a isKnownSentinel() always</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00169" /><CodeLine lineNumber="169"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// returns \\c false tracking is off.  Sentinel tracking steals a bit from the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00170" /><CodeLine lineNumber="170"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &quot;prev&quot; link, which adds a mask operation when decrementing an iterator, but</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00171" /><CodeLine lineNumber="171"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// enables bug-finding assertions in \\a ilist&#95;iterator.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00172" /><CodeLine lineNumber="172"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00173" /><CodeLine lineNumber="173"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// To turn sentinel tracking on all the time, pass in the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00174" /><CodeLine lineNumber="174"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// ilist&#95;sentinel&#95;tracking&lt;true&gt; template parameter.  This also enables the \\a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="175"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// isSentinel() function.  The same option must be passed to the intrusive</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00176" /><CodeLine lineNumber="176"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// list.  (ilist&#95;sentinel&#95;tracking&lt;false&gt; turns sentinel tracking off all the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00177" /><CodeLine lineNumber="177"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// time.)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00178" /><CodeLine lineNumber="178"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00179" /><CodeLine lineNumber="179"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// A type can inherit from ilist&#95;node multiple times by passing in different</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00180" /><CodeLine lineNumber="180"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\a ilist&#95;tag options.  This allows a single instance to be inserted into</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00181" /><CodeLine lineNumber="181"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// multiple lists simultaneously, where each list is given the same tag.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00182" /><CodeLine lineNumber="182"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00183" /><CodeLine lineNumber="183"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\example</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00184" /><CodeLine lineNumber="184"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// struct A &#123;&#125;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00185" /><CodeLine lineNumber="185"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// struct B &#123;&#125;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00186" /><CodeLine lineNumber="186"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// struct N : ilist&#95;node&lt;N, ilist&#95;tag&lt;A&gt;&gt;, ilist&#95;node&lt;N, ilist&#95;tag&lt;B&gt;&gt; &#123;&#125;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00187" /><CodeLine lineNumber="187"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00188" /><CodeLine lineNumber="188"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// void foo() &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00189" /><CodeLine lineNumber="189"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   simple&#95;ilist&lt;N, ilist&#95;tag&lt;A&gt;&gt; ListA;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00190" /><CodeLine lineNumber="190"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   simple&#95;ilist&lt;N, ilist&#95;tag&lt;B&gt;&gt; ListB;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00191" /><CodeLine lineNumber="191"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   N N1;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00192" /><CodeLine lineNumber="192"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   ListA.push&#95;back(N1);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00193" /><CodeLine lineNumber="193"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   ListB.push&#95;back(N1);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00194" /><CodeLine lineNumber="194"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00195" /><CodeLine lineNumber="195"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\endexample</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00196" /><CodeLine lineNumber="196"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00197" /><CodeLine lineNumber="197"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// When the \\a ilist&#95;parent&lt;ParentTy&gt; option is passed to an ilist&#95;node and the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00198" /><CodeLine lineNumber="198"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// owning ilist, each node contains a pointer to the ilist&#39;s owner. This adds</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00199" /><CodeLine lineNumber="199"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\a getParent() and \\a setParent(ParentTy&#42;) methods to the ilist&#95;node, which</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00200" /><CodeLine lineNumber="200"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// will be used for node access by the ilist if the node class publicly</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00201" /><CodeLine lineNumber="201"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// inherits from \\a ilist&#95;node&#95;with&#95;parent. By default, setParent() is not</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00202" /><CodeLine lineNumber="202"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// automatically called by the ilist; a SymbolTableList will call setParent()</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00203" /><CodeLine lineNumber="203"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// on inserted nodes, but the sentinel must still be manually set after the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00204" /><CodeLine lineNumber="204"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// list is created (e.g. SymTabList.end()-&gt;setParent(Parent)).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00205" /><CodeLine lineNumber="205"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
